dancers with spotty records,
that kind of thing?

11:44.960 --> 11:45.949
Who's asking?

11:45.960 --> 11:47.700
Iam.

11:47.710 --> 11:49.610
I'm a, uh,
private investigator.

11:49.620 --> 11:50.746
Dex Parios.

11:50.750 --> 11:52.240
My business card.

11:52.250 --> 11:53.956
I'm here on, uh,
Ginger's behalf.

11:55.330 --> 11:57.992
Eh, I'm sorry.
That's my only one. So...

11:58.000 --> 11:59.490
Thank you.

11:59.500 --> 12:02.663
Let me guess --
you're her new best friend?

12:02.670 --> 12:05.036
What if we are friends? Is that
a crime here at the 5.0.3.?

12:06.420 --> 12:07.739
[ Computer beeps ]

12:07.750 --> 12:09.661
Oh.
Here we go.

12:09.670 --> 12:11.786
Enrique Bedoya.

12:13.290 --> 12:14.746
Made some threats.

12:16.380 --> 12:17.074
Okay.

12:19.210 --> 12:21.246
How long did you work
at Hold the Meat?

12:21.250 --> 12:22.706
Five years.
Hmm.

12:22.710 --> 12:24.780
Why'd you leave?
Fell off the stage.

12:24.790 --> 12:26.826
Tore my ACL.

12:26.830 --> 12:28.957
Exact same injury Tom Brady
suffered in 2008.

12:28.960 --> 12:31.030
No kidding. Hmm.

12:31.040 --> 12:34.612
So, uh, what was your
relationship like with Ginger?

12:34.620 --> 12:36.576
Fine. Great.
She's like a mother to me.

12:36.580 --> 12:38.286
[ Chuckles ]

12:38.290 --> 12:41.077
Then why did you tell her
you would break her in half

12:41.080 --> 12:44.322
if it didn't mean that the world
would be left with two of her?

12:44.330 --> 12:45.991
[ Sighs ]
I can explain that.

12:46.000 --> 12:47.740
Please do.

12:47.750 --> 12:49.877
I went back to the club with the
estimates for the knee surgery,

12:49.880 --> 12:51.074
and she said
I was on my own

12:51.080 --> 12:52.570
because I was
a private contractor

12:52.580 --> 12:54.912
and some other legal mumbo jumbo
I didn't understand,

12:54.920 --> 12:56.956
and I lost my temper.

12:56.960 --> 12:58.746
But I apologized
to Ginger.

12:58.750 --> 13:00.069
She's still mad
about that?

13:00.080 --> 13:02.958
Oh, she's mad that someone's
stealing from her club.

13:02.960 --> 13:04.029
That's what
this is about?

13:04.040 --> 13:05.280
Yep, indeedy.

13:05.290 --> 13:06.370
[ Chuckles ]

13:06.380 --> 13:08.951
I'm not perfect.
I've made mistakes.

13:13.670 --> 13:15.206
Hey, Jimmy.

13:15.210 --> 13:17.747
For your husband.
The heartless bastard.

13:17.750 --> 13:19.911
The two of you
still betting on golf?

13:19.920 --> 13:22.320
We were playing in Nassau,
three ways.

13:22.330 --> 13:24.412
The front nine and back nine
canceled each other and then --

13:24.420 --> 13:26.490
Alright, I'm gonna just
take that as a yes.

13:26.500 --> 13:28.661
So, let's hear it.

13:28.670 --> 13:29.989
What do you mean?

13:30.000 --> 13:33.072
Well, I'm guessing this tequila
is only half of the reason

13:33.080 --> 13:34.456
why you made
the trip down here.

13:36.620 --> 13:37.826
Okay, yeah.

13:37.830 --> 13:39.661
I've got some concerns.

13:39.670 --> 13:41.490
Okay.

13:41.500 --> 13:43.320
I know Hoffman's your protg
or whatever

13:43.330 --> 13:45.491
and you're grooming him
to be a boss,

13:45.500 --> 13:48.958
but let me tell you
what other cops are saying.

13:48.960 --> 13:51.076
He don't trust
anybody but himself,

13:51.080 --> 13:53.708
which is why he does
that lone wolf act of his.

13:53.710 --> 13:55.610
And you know I'm right.

13:55.620 --> 13:57.997
Normally,
I couldn't give a rat's ass,

13:58.000 --> 13:59.820
but not on a case
like this.

13:59.830 --> 14:01.491
Look, I told him to
cooperate.

14:01.500 --> 14:03.377
You heard me say it
in the room.

14:03.380 --> 14:04.870
You just got to give him
a chance, Jimmy.

14:04.880 --> 14:06.416
I have.

14:06.420 --> 14:08.741
Called him twice, texted.
No response.

14:10.710 --> 14:13.611
And he's got that mouthy CI
who walks all over him?

14:13.620 --> 14:16.327
Hoffman's trusting a case
this big to him?

14:16.330 --> 14:18.457
Bobby, I know drugs
and I know informants,

14:18.460 --> 14:20.166
and that douchebag
has his own agenda.

14:20.170 --> 14:21.785
Believe me.

14:21.790 --> 14:23.109
Okay.

14:23.120 --> 14:24.826
Got it.

14:27.540 --> 14:31.499
[Tool clicking ]

14:31.500 --> 14:32.990
I think it's
the oil pressure switch.

14:33.000 --> 14:35.616
You're gonna have to take
the engine out.

14:35.620 --> 14:37.417
It's the thermostat
O-rIng.

14:37.420 --> 14:39.376
You're still gonna have to
take the engine out.

14:39.380 --> 14:40.995
[ Sighs ] Smart ass.

14:42.620 --> 14:43.951
How'd you get
into cars, Max?

14:43.960 --> 14:45.951
Fixing or stealing?

14:45.960 --> 14:48.076
Figured they went hand-in-hand.
They did with me, at least.

14:48.080 --> 14:49.570
My pops.

14:49.580 --> 14:50.956
Not right away, though.

14:50.960 --> 14:53.246
First, he taught me
the Melon Drop con.

14:53.250 --> 14:54.877
The Melon Drop con?
What's that?

14:54.880 --> 14:56.450
[ Chuckles ]
Never heard of it?

14:56.460 --> 14:58.109
No.

14:58.120 --> 15:01.999
My dad would buy me a watermelon
at a farmer's market,

15:02.000 --> 15:05.993
then I'd spot a couple
that looked like they had cash,

15:06.000 --> 15:07.319
had them run into me,

15:07.330 --> 15:09.912
the watermelon would drop,
crack open.

15:09.920 --> 15:12.241
I'd start bawling,
and, you know,

15:12.250 --> 15:13.956
20 bucks later...

15:13.960 --> 15:16.417
Smart.
[ Chuckles ]

15:16.420 --> 15:18.911
How old were you?
8.

15:18.920 --> 15:22.617
Then it was on to pickpocketing,
which I was serviceable at,

15:22.620 --> 15:27.068
then three card Monte,
which I still don't get,

15:27.080 --> 15:29.958
and then finally, cars.

15:29.960 --> 15:31.075
Love at first sight.

15:31.080 --> 15:32.707
No doubt.

15:32.710 --> 15:34.450
[Tool clicking ]

15:34.460 --> 15:37.452
Where's your dad now?

15:37.460 --> 15:38.165
Leavenworth.

15:41.460 --> 15:44.031
Did everything I could
not to end up like him.

15:46.000 --> 15:48.241
Here I am.

15:48.250 --> 15:51.208
Believe me, I get it.

15:51.210 --> 15:53.747
I'm not a drug dealer,
though.

15:53.750 --> 15:55.570
Never was.

15:55.580 --> 15:57.411
Okay.
I mean it.

15:57.420 --> 15:59.490
That stuff just dropped
in our lap.

15:59.500 --> 16:01.036
Gotcha.

16:01.040 --> 16:04.248
I can't believe we're about to
drop 20 kilos out on the street.

16:08.670 --> 16:10.035
So, why don't you
just flush it?

16:10.040 --> 16:12.031
[ Leo talking indistinctly]

16:14.290 --> 16:15.575
[ Exhales sharply]

16:15.580 --> 16:16.990
Not my call.

16:22.620 --> 16:23.826
Look,
I'll see you around.

16:23.830 --> 16:24.785
Yeah. For sure.

16:29.920 --> 16:31.740
[APM's "Watch Her Dance"
plays ]

16:36.540 --> 16:38.701
This is hard.

16:38.710 --> 16:41.281
Hard? No.

16:41.290 --> 16:43.201
Tacos Chicharrn is hard.

16:45.040 --> 16:47.417
What about
a nice cupcake?

16:47.420 --> 16:48.535
No.

16:48.540 --> 16:49.916
Rice Krispie treat?

16:49.920 --> 16:51.740
No. Baked Alaska!

16:51.750 --> 16:53.320
[ Whimpering ] Okay.

16:53.330 --> 16:54.536
Okay.

16:54.540 --> 16:55.871
We try again.

16:55.880 --> 16:57.575
Add one cup of flour
at a time.

16:58.750 --> 17:01.321
Slowly.
Easy does it, killer.

17:01.330 --> 17:02.615
Okay.

17:02.620 --> 17:04.781
Let it mix.

17:04.790 --> 17:06.781
Wait, but keep your eyes
on it at all times. Trust me.

17:08.170 --> 17:09.239
Okay.

17:11.040 --> 17:12.826
[ Exhales sharply]

17:12.830 --> 17:14.661
When did you meet Dex?

17:14.670 --> 17:16.786
[ Chuckles ]

17:16.790 --> 17:18.917
When she was like 15.

17:18.920 --> 17:21.957
I was working at a bookstore
on Burnside back then.

17:21.960 --> 17:23.279
Someone started
putting the Bibles

17:23.290 --> 17:25.747
in the fiction section
every day.

17:25.750 --> 17:27.160
Then I caught Dex
red-handed.

17:27.170 --> 17:29.240
She took off
like a bat outta infierno.

17:29.250 --> 17:31.036
[ Chuckling ]
That's Spanish for "Hell."

17:31.040 --> 17:32.780
Si. [ Chuckles ]

17:32.790 --> 17:34.826
She was fast,
but I was motivated.

17:34.830 --> 17:36.821
I tackled her
in the parking lot.

17:36.830 --> 17:38.707
Ithought
I saved the clay.

17:38.710 --> 17:40.416
Then I got fired.

17:40.420 --> 17:42.991
Turns out what I did is
something called snmple assault.

17:44.540 --> 17:46.246
So, you knew our parents?

17:49.330 --> 17:51.207
I did.

17:51.210 --> 17:52.609
Nice people.

18:01.330 --> 18:03.707
Hey, so,
I met with Enrique today.

18:03.710 --> 18:05.746
Aw, Love Bug.
How's his knee?

18:05.750 --> 18:06.739
Oh, thank you.

18:06.750 --> 18:08.411
Um, good, I think.

18:08.420 --> 18:09.956
Uh, was Enrique
working at the club

18:09.960 --> 18:11.370
when the money
was disappearing?

18:11.380 --> 18:13.200
Maybe. I'd have to
check the books.

18:13.210 --> 18:15.610
Oh!
I have something for you.

18:15.620 --> 18:16.450
For me?

18:21.540 --> 18:22.700
A necklace?

18:22.710 --> 18:23.995
[ Chuckling ] Ohh.

18:24.000 --> 18:25.490
Whoa, Ginger.

18:25.500 --> 18:27.411
I know you have your own style,
and I dig it,

18:27.420 --> 18:29.240
but every girl should have
a diamond around their neck.

18:29.250 --> 18:30.410
Oh.

18:30.420 --> 18:32.820
It's just been sitting
in my drawer for 15 years.

18:32.830 --> 18:34.957
This is -- This is too much.
I can't accept this.

18:34.960 --> 18:37.702
Plus, the P.I. Board has a rule
against accepting gifts, so --

18:37.710 --> 18:39.746
They'll never know.
May I?

18:39.750 --> 18:41.115
[ Scoffs, clears throat ]

18:41.120 --> 18:45.329
Remember, never apologize
for being a strong single woman

18:45.330 --> 18:47.616
with your own money,
your own life,

18:47.620 --> 18:50.418
your own business,
your own good time,

18:50.420 --> 18:52.376
because you're gonna encounter
a lot of people

18:52.380 --> 18:54.280
who are threatened by it,
and they'll try to
take it away from you

18:54.290 --> 18:55.780
just to make them
feel bigger.

18:57.210 --> 18:58.245
Take a look.

19:01.920 --> 19:03.114
[ Sighs ]

19:03.120 --> 19:04.701
[ Chuckles ]

19:04.710 --> 19:05.699
I love it.

19:05.710 --> 19:06.574
Thanks, Ginger.

19:06.580 --> 19:07.956
[ Rhythmic knock on door ]

19:07.960 --> 19:09.825
Make two more drinks.

19:09.830 --> 19:11.206
Two more?
Uh-huh.

19:12.420 --> 19:13.876
[ Chuckling ] Hello!

19:15.290 --> 19:17.702
I figured
you'd want Ford.

19:17.710 --> 19:19.280
She's had her eye on you.

19:19.290 --> 19:21.372
Wait, doesn't she work for
the Census Bureau's office?

19:21.380 --> 19:24.531
[ Chuckles ] Oh, well,
she's off the clock.

19:24.540 --> 19:26.167
Okay.

19:26.170 --> 19:27.410
Make memories,
not babies.

19:31.040 --> 19:32.280
What is happening?

19:36.580 --> 19:37.820
O...kay.

19:41.460 --> 19:42.415
Hi.

19:42.420 --> 19:43.876
Hey.

19:48.620 --> 19:49.917
I-I'm sorry.

19:49.920 --> 19:54.664
I-I guess I just can't
when it's...arranged.

19:54.670 --> 19:56.069
This is a first
for me, too.

19:56.080 --> 19:57.570
Oh. Escorting?

19:57.580 --> 19:59.787
[ Chuckling ] No.
No, being turned down.

19:59.790 --> 20:01.200
Well...

20:01.210 --> 20:03.781
[Thumping,
Ginger moaning in distance ]

20:06.580 --> 20:07.569
Yeah.

20:07.580 --> 20:08.990
[Thumping, moaning continue ]

20:09.000 --> 20:10.740
[ Chuckles ]

20:10.750 --> 20:12.570
Ginger's the best, huh?
Oh, yeah.

20:12.580 --> 20:14.741
She is, uh --
She is an interesting one.

20:14.750 --> 20:15.910
That is for sure.
[ Chuckles ]

20:15.920 --> 20:17.911
She is the best.
The best.

20:17.920 --> 20:19.160
Yeah.
She is really...

20:19.170 --> 20:20.785
[Thumping, moaning continue ]

20:20.790 --> 20:22.496
...great.
[ Chuckles ]

20:22.500 --> 20:24.491
Uh...

20:24.500 --> 20:27.458
Anyone from your work
not feel the same way?

20:28.880 --> 20:32.418
No.
Everybody loves Ginger.

20:32.420 --> 20:35.787
Well, anybody that you think
might want to steal from her?

20:35.790 --> 20:36.950
Steal?

20:36.960 --> 20:38.746
No way.

20:38.750 --> 20:40.411
Maybe Enrique?

20:40.420 --> 20:41.705
No.

20:41.710 --> 20:44.031
I saw him the other day.
He's moved on.

20:44.040 --> 20:45.280
You saw him
the other day?

20:45.290 --> 20:46.166
Yeah.

20:48.880 --> 20:52.168
Well, m-maybe...
it was longer than that.

20:52.170 --> 20:54.035
No, you know what?
I'm -- [ Chuckles ]

20:54.040 --> 20:55.416
I'm thinking
about another dancer.

20:55.420 --> 20:56.535
Right.
[ Door opens ]

20:56.540 --> 20:58.781
Yo! Party people!

20:58.790 --> 21:00.610
What's up with all
the talky-talk?

21:00.620 --> 21:03.612
Yeah, it's not, um...
it's just not my style.

21:03.620 --> 21:05.247
Yet.
That's my new goal.

21:05.250 --> 21:06.786
I'm gonna show you
how to have a good time.

21:06.790 --> 21:07.745
Operation Dex.

21:07.750 --> 21:09.160
Cannot wait.

21:09.170 --> 21:10.819
Ford, are you coming?

21:10.830 --> 21:11.615
Yes.

21:14.420 --> 21:16.957
Mmm! Yummy!

21:16.960 --> 21:18.666
It's still early.

21:18.670 --> 21:20.661
See you tomorrow.
Mm. Okay.

21:20.670 --> 21:22.069
You get in there!

21:22.080 --> 21:24.571
I can't -- I don't --
You get right in there!

21:24.580 --> 21:25.410
[ Door closes ]

21:30.790 --> 21:32.417
You need something?

21:32.420 --> 21:34.160
Oh, hey, there you are.

21:34.170 --> 21:36.570
I was looking for a copy
of your CI's case file.

21:36.580 --> 21:38.536
I don't share case files
on my CIs.

21:38.540 --> 21:40.167
We're running this thing
together.

21:40.170 --> 21:41.376
I should be up to speed.

21:41.380 --> 21:43.075
You will be --
when I need you.

21:43.080 --> 21:45.537
Look, I'm not gonna hog
the spotlight on this.

21:45.540 --> 21:47.531
You can parade the suspect
in front of the lieutenant,

21:47.540 --> 21:48.996
show her
what a good cop you are.

21:49.000 --> 21:50.877
I'm just trying to
get drugs off the street,

21:50.880 --> 21:52.495
and I've got just
a tiny bit more experience

21:52.500 --> 21:53.660
doing that than you.

21:53.670 --> 21:56.207
When I need you,
I'll call you.

21:57.250 --> 21:58.069
Okay.

21:59.420 --> 22:00.819
Hey.

22:00.830 --> 22:02.570
Are you related to
Lionel Hoffman?

22:02.580 --> 22:03.660
Defense attorney?

22:03.670 --> 22:05.535
He's my father.

22:05.540 --> 22:07.872
Ah.
Now it all makes sense.

22:07.880 --> 22:09.108
Meaning what?

22:09.120 --> 22:10.371
Nothing.

22:10.380 --> 22:11.870
He's a good man.

22:29.250 --> 22:30.786
[ Engine sputters ]

22:30.790 --> 22:31.745
Oh, no, no, no.

22:31.750 --> 22:33.820
Come on!

22:33.830 --> 22:34.910
[ Engine sputters ]

22:34.920 --> 22:37.070
Oh, I gotta pee.
Come on!

22:37.080 --> 22:40.243
[ Click ]
'Cause there's somethin'
we forgot to say to you

22:40.250 --> 22:41.615
Ugh.

22:41.620 --> 22:47.536
Sisters are doin' it
for themselves

22:47.540 --> 22:50.919
Standin' on
their own two feet

22:50.920 --> 22:53.957
And ringin'
on their own bells

22:56.960 --> 23:01.408
Sisters are doin' it
for themselves

23:03.000 --> 23:06.117
[ Car doors open ]
Now, this is a song

23:06.120 --> 23:10.568
To celebrate

23:10.580 --> 23:12.992
Sisters are doin' it
for themselves

23:13.000 --> 23:14.661
[ Knock on door ]

23:14.670 --> 23:17.116
Aretha Franklin: Thank you, all.
I'll get it myself.

23:17.120 --> 23:18.451
Well.

23:18.460 --> 23:20.667
This isn't suspicious
at all.

23:20.670 --> 23:22.410
Census taker, my ass!

23:22.420 --> 23:24.069
Yeah.
Well, you got me there.

23:24.080 --> 23:26.116
You're a spy.
Private investigator.

23:26.120 --> 23:28.611
Ugh, man, I wish I was a spy.
That'd be pretty cool, huh?

23:28.620 --> 23:31.077
It's still
a breach of privacy.

23:31.080 --> 23:33.617
Was almost sleeping with Ford
part of your investigation, too?

23:33.620 --> 23:34.951
Okay, okay.

23:34.960 --> 23:37.667
That was not my choice,
and I did turn it down.

23:37.670 --> 23:39.240
Right, Ford?

23:39.250 --> 23:42.879
Guys, I have been through all
of the security footage, okay?

23:42.880 --> 23:45.781
At the end of each shift,
each one of your bikini briefs

23:45.790 --> 23:48.532
is way bulgier
than when you started.

23:48.540 --> 23:50.747
That's where you've been
stuffing the extra cash.

23:50.750 --> 23:51.535
Am I right?

23:53.380 --> 23:55.575
So, tell me what is
going on, and we can keep
the cops out of this,

23:55.580 --> 23:57.036
'cause that's
where we're headed.

24:02.250 --> 24:04.957
You're never gonna
divide us.
[ Door opens ]

24:04.960 --> 24:07.076
We stand together,
as brothers.
[ Door closes ]

24:11.750 --> 24:12.876
What --
Ohh!

24:14.460 --> 24:16.371
I don't want to go to jail
over this.

24:16.380 --> 24:17.608
Great speech.

24:17.620 --> 24:18.746
Just tell her.

24:21.080 --> 24:22.877
Ginger pushed me off the stage
that night,

24:22.880 --> 24:24.666
right after I told her
she needed help.

24:24.670 --> 24:27.286
She'd been drinking
more and more, until
now it's every night.

24:27.290 --> 24:28.780
Then why didn't you just
file a report?

24:28.790 --> 24:30.166
It's the only
male revue club in town.

24:30.170 --> 24:32.377
Rock the boat,
and you're out.

24:32.380 --> 24:33.495
I'm a single dad.

24:33.500 --> 24:35.286
Between daycare, clothes,
food, rent,

24:35.290 --> 24:36.871
and now
the hospital bills --

24:36.880 --> 24:39.826
We've all been skimming a little
for Enrique to keep him afloat.

24:39.830 --> 24:42.742
She likes you.
She'll listen to you.

24:42.750 --> 24:44.115
Can you talk to her?

24:46.500 --> 24:48.456
[ Orquesta Panamericana's
"El Charlatan" plays ]

24:54.170 --> 24:55.990
No, my friend.
One more minute.

24:56.000 --> 24:57.285
Can't hurry genius.

24:57.290 --> 24:58.575
Outside a sharp knife,

24:58.580 --> 25:00.821
patience is a chef's
most valuable tool.

25:00.830 --> 25:04.914
Patience for the process,
patience to let flavors blossom.

25:07.880 --> 25:09.416
Why'd they leave?

25:09.420 --> 25:10.159
VVho?

25:10.170 --> 25:11.706
My parents.

25:13.750 --> 25:16.537
You know, that's something
you should talk to Dex about.

25:16.540 --> 25:18.496
Dex doesn't like
talking about it.

25:20.880 --> 25:22.950
I'm sorry, hermano.

25:22.960 --> 25:24.166
Maybe she will one day.

25:34.960 --> 25:36.916
Hey, Ginger.
Mm!

25:36.920 --> 25:37.739
What's up, girlfriend?

25:37.750 --> 25:39.536
Well, I figured it out.

25:39.540 --> 25:40.529
[ Gasps ]

25:40.540 --> 25:42.952
Oh, my God!
Tell me.

25:42.960 --> 25:44.825
Well, uh, a couple
unnamed strippers

25:44.830 --> 25:47.958
were taking a little off the top
to help Enrique with his bills.

25:47.960 --> 25:49.325
Unnamed?
What do you mean "unnamed"?

25:49.330 --> 25:51.161
Well, I mean,
I kind of know who they are,

25:51.170 --> 25:52.455
but I think I have
a solution

25:52.460 --> 25:54.496
where we don't have to drop
a bomb on anyone's head.

25:54.500 --> 25:55.615
Okay.

25:55.620 --> 25:57.247
You have
a morale problem.

25:57.250 --> 25:58.990
The Marines didn't teach me
anything about strippers,

25:59.000 --> 26:00.911
but morale, I do know.

26:00.920 --> 26:02.785
A morale problem?
Mm-hmm.

26:02.790 --> 26:05.873
Last I checked, I hired a PI,
not a therapist.

26:08.170 --> 26:10.035
Ginger, I'm telling you this
as a friend.

26:10.040 --> 26:11.416
Bring Enrique back,

26:11.420 --> 26:13.069
put him behind the bar
until his knee heals up.

26:13.080 --> 26:15.036
He just --
He wants an apology.

26:15.040 --> 26:16.667
For what?
[ Exhales sharply]

26:16.670 --> 26:19.491
Well, his version is that you
shoved him off the stage.

26:19.500 --> 26:22.287
[ Scoffs ]
Regardless of --
of that,

26:22.290 --> 26:23.917
just hold
a big team meeting.

26:23.920 --> 26:27.162
Tell the guys that you value
and appreciate them

26:27.170 --> 26:29.741
and it's a fresh start,
starting today.

26:29.750 --> 26:30.910
It'll pay off tenfold.

26:30.920 --> 26:32.319
Well, eh, fivefold.

26:32.330 --> 26:34.412
It's gonna get better around
here, is what I'm trying to say.

26:34.420 --> 26:36.911
Because the guys seem like
they're good guys,

26:36.920 --> 26:38.569
and they care about you.

26:38.580 --> 26:41.572
In fact, from what I gathered,
they're, uh...

26:41.580 --> 26:43.992
[ Clears throat ]
they're concerned about you.

26:45.080 --> 26:46.707
I'm really sad right now.

26:46.710 --> 26:48.166
Why?

26:48.170 --> 26:49.660
Ithought
you were different,

26:49.670 --> 26:51.877
but you're just like
all the other haters.

26:51.880 --> 26:54.371
You just can't handle seeing me
live the life you want.

26:54.380 --> 26:56.200
Um...no. No, that's --
that's not it.

26:56.210 --> 26:57.495
Oh, sure it is.

26:57.500 --> 26:59.411
You want me to have
a small life, like yours,

26:59.420 --> 27:01.285
to make you
feel better about yourself.

27:01.290 --> 27:03.611
But guess what, toots.
Not gonna happen.

27:03.620 --> 27:05.827
Okay, that's fine.
We can just stick to the case.

27:05.830 --> 27:07.377
We're not
sticking to the case.

27:07.380 --> 27:08.950
You're no longer
working for me.

27:08.960 --> 27:10.029
We're no longer "friends."

27:11.540 --> 27:14.031
Okay, Ginger, I'm just trying to
help you here, you know?

27:14.040 --> 27:15.576
[ Chuckles ]

27:15.580 --> 27:17.662
You should
see your face right now.

27:17.670 --> 27:20.878
You're all like, "Oh,
I just royally screwed up."

27:20.880 --> 27:24.873
You almost had the golden ticket
of hanging out with me.

27:24.880 --> 27:25.949
That's gone.

27:27.540 --> 27:30.748
Uh...you know, I-I think
that you have some issues,

27:30.750 --> 27:32.536
you know, either with
abandonment or anger.

27:32.540 --> 27:34.781
I mean, certainly --
certainly with anger,

27:34.790 --> 27:37.111
but obviously, you don't want to
talk about them,

27:37.120 --> 27:38.576
so --
You know what?

27:38.580 --> 27:40.491
You might want to
look in the mirror next time

27:40.500 --> 27:42.286
before you tell somebody else
how to live their life.

27:44.790 --> 27:46.326
No wonder
your brother left you.

27:49.210 --> 27:50.700
Wow.

27:50.710 --> 27:51.825
You're fired.

27:51.830 --> 27:52.876
Uh --

27:52.880 --> 27:54.700
Get the hell out.

28:03.790 --> 28:05.781
Hey.
Where's Grey?

28:05.790 --> 28:06.700
Haven't seen him.

28:06.710 --> 28:08.109
What are you drinking?

28:09.620 --> 28:10.917
You're new.

28:10.920 --> 28:12.376
This is true.

28:12.380 --> 28:13.608
Cool.

28:13.620 --> 28:14.575
Well, I'm, uh, Dex.

28:16.710 --> 28:17.529
Grey's friend.

28:19.620 --> 28:20.780
Ansel's sister.

28:20.790 --> 28:22.667
Dude, I just started
yesterday.
Okay.

28:22.670 --> 28:24.820
Well, uh, did Grey
mention the part

28:24.830 --> 28:26.661
where Dex gets a drink
for free?

28:26.670 --> 28:28.240
No, he did not.
[ Door opens ]

28:28.250 --> 28:30.206
IPA.
Which one?

28:30.210 --> 28:32.075
Coldest one you got.
[ Door closes ]

28:32.080 --> 28:34.071
[ Sighs ]
Nowhere to go but up.

28:35.290 --> 28:37.030
Miss Parios?
Yeah?

28:37.040 --> 28:39.497
Harriet Straw.
DPSST.

28:39.500 --> 28:43.209
Oh. Yeah, the, uh, Department
of Public...Safety,

28:43.210 --> 28:44.529
um...

28:44.540 --> 28:46.701
The PI licensing place.

28:46.710 --> 28:47.995
You work with Janice?

28:48.000 --> 28:49.661
Janet
Right.

28:49.670 --> 28:51.911
Were you recently hired
by a Ginger Lloyd?

28:51.920 --> 28:53.876
Yeah.
Why? What's going on?

28:53.880 --> 28:56.326
She filed a complaint
against you.
Wait, what?

28:56.330 --> 28:58.958
Consequently, our office has
opened a formal investigation.

28:58.960 --> 29:00.996
W-What do -- What do you mean?
How -- How formal?

29:02.120 --> 29:03.826
Formal.

29:03.830 --> 29:06.822
This will be thoroughly, fairly,
and promptly investigated.

29:06.830 --> 29:08.491
What did Ginger say I did?

29:08.500 --> 29:10.286
Trying to sleep
with one of her employees,

29:10.290 --> 29:12.030
general incompetence,
accepting a gift --

29:12.040 --> 29:13.780
a diamond necklace,
specifically --

29:13.790 --> 29:15.576
and drinking on the job.

29:15.580 --> 29:18.458
Okay, the first two things
are lies,

29:18.460 --> 29:21.452
the third is iffy at best,
and the fourth is a joke

29:21.460 --> 29:24.076
because she was the_ one
who was constantly drinking.

29:24.080 --> 29:26.207
She's not a private investigator
licensed by our office.

29:26.210 --> 29:27.575
She can drink
as much as she wants.

29:27.580 --> 29:28.911
Fair point.
That's a fair point.

29:28.920 --> 29:31.036
If her claims
are substantiated

29:31.040 --> 29:33.326
and Ms. Lloyd
pushes hard enough,

29:33.330 --> 29:34.877
your license could
get permanently revoked.

29:36.500 --> 29:38.320
Have a great
rest of your day.

29:40.670 --> 29:42.206
[ Door opens ]

29:44.920 --> 29:46.490
Yo, Hoffman,
we have a problem.

29:46.500 --> 29:47.910
Yeah, you don't
answer my calls.

29:47.920 --> 29:49.490
No, it's a little bit
bigger than that.

29:49.500 --> 29:52.116
The crew is sitting on
20 kilos of heroin.

29:52.120 --> 29:53.326
What?

29:53.330 --> 29:54.661
Are you sure
you heard that right?

29:54.670 --> 29:55.876
Yes, I'm sure.

29:55.880 --> 29:57.575
That's over a million,
street value.

29:57.580 --> 30:00.208
Who in Portland is trying to
move that much dope?

30:00.210 --> 30:03.202
Short list.
Heaw players.

30:03.210 --> 30:04.746
Okay, look,
you need to do

30:04.750 --> 30:06.786
what you were gonna do
24 hours ago.

30:06.790 --> 30:08.166
Force their hand.

30:08.170 --> 30:10.491
They need to
take your buyer today.

30:10.500 --> 30:12.741
If they don't,
you pull out.

30:12.750 --> 30:15.571
I'll lock them all up, and then
I'll start flipping people.

30:15.580 --> 30:16.706
Hey, Hoffman?

30:18.080 --> 30:20.071
What if I get Max to
cooperate?

30:21.500 --> 30:23.240
Is she wobbling?

30:23.250 --> 30:24.660
Yeah, a little.

30:24.670 --> 30:27.241
Or is she just putting on an act
to see if you're a rat

30:27.250 --> 30:28.490
and then
she tells her boyfriend,

30:28.500 --> 30:30.036
and you end up with a bullet
in the back of the head?

30:32.120 --> 30:33.701
Don't overthink it, Grey.

30:43.000 --> 30:44.160
Hey, Lieutenant.
Hey.

30:44.170 --> 30:46.570
What'd your CI
have to say?

30:46.580 --> 30:49.538
I'll, uh, type it up.
CC you on it.

30:49.540 --> 30:51.417
This is exactly
what I was talking about.

30:51.420 --> 30:53.456
Why you pushing so hard
on this, man?

30:53.460 --> 30:55.246
Well, the question is, why
aren't you sharing information?

30:55.250 --> 30:57.536
Which I believe
was conveyed to you

30:57.540 --> 30:59.826
as a direct order
and not a request.

30:59.830 --> 31:01.411
Respectfully,
Lieutenant...

31:01.420 --> 31:03.615
I don't trust this dude.

31:03.620 --> 31:04.951
Meaning what?

31:04.960 --> 31:06.496
Meaning you try to
bulldoze into this

31:06.500 --> 31:08.286
like you do
every other case I read about,

31:08.290 --> 31:11.168
and I can't have that --
not with my CI inside.

31:11.170 --> 31:12.740
I read about you,
too, kid,

31:12.750 --> 31:15.162
and maybe this is all about you
making up for the fact

31:15.170 --> 31:17.035
that you got
your last CI killed.

31:17.040 --> 31:18.416
Darius? _ _
Am I pronouncmg It right?

31:18.420 --> 31:19.455
Know what?
What?

31:19.460 --> 31:20.165
Enough.

31:23.250 --> 31:25.707
You need to share information,
Hoffman,

31:25.710 --> 31:27.917
or you're gonna
lose this case entirely.

31:33.830 --> 31:35.536
This crew is trying to
move 20 kilos.

31:35.540 --> 31:37.576
And I need to know
the location of this crew,

31:37.580 --> 31:38.820
and I need
to know it now.

31:38.830 --> 31:40.115
Really?

31:40.120 --> 31:41.667
Now you're pissing me off.

31:43.460 --> 31:44.666
Sorry, Lieutenant.

31:46.710 --> 31:47.950
Just keep me
in the loop.

31:50.540 --> 31:53.452
...mind's like a window
looking into my brain

31:53.460 --> 31:55.030
[ Clears throat ]

31:55.040 --> 31:57.281
[ Indistinct conversations ]

31:57.290 --> 32:02.034
Taking all my time and leaving
nothing but my pain

32:05.960 --> 32:07.496
I gotta get away

32:07.500 --> 32:08.569
Dex?

32:10.620 --> 32:11.871
Yeah.

32:11.880 --> 32:13.416
Poppy.
We talked on the phone.

32:13.420 --> 32:14.876
Oh. Right. Hey.

32:14.880 --> 32:17.872
Um...I forgot to put
some money in my meter.

32:17.880 --> 32:19.029
Be right back.
Right.

32:19.040 --> 32:20.576
You know,
it took me three times

32:20.580 --> 32:22.616
before I gave
one of these meetings a shot.

32:22.620 --> 32:24.952
So why don't I save you
some trips, Marine?

32:24.960 --> 32:26.075
Get your ass in here.

32:28.960 --> 32:32.111
I gotta get away

32:35.750 --> 32:37.706
See?
It's no big deal.

32:37.710 --> 32:38.995
Once a week, we meet.

32:39.000 --> 32:40.740
There's a Facebook group,
so we get vets

32:40.750 --> 32:42.786
and active military
from all over the country.

32:42.790 --> 32:44.576
They drop in
whenever they're in town.

32:44.580 --> 32:47.413
There's no pressure.
It's informal.

32:47.420 --> 32:48.990
And if you're anything like me,
you'll be surprised

32:49.000 --> 32:51.116
at how great it feels
to be around other veterans,

32:51.120 --> 32:52.917
'cause they get it.

32:54.290 --> 32:57.373
Why are you here?
Did something happen?

32:57.380 --> 32:58.870
Oh, um...
[ Clears throat ]

32:58.880 --> 33:01.451
Honestly, uh...

33:01.460 --> 33:03.496
for the first time
since I got back, I've --

33:03.500 --> 33:05.536
I've found something
that I'm good at.

33:05.540 --> 33:08.828
And today, someone decided
to take that away from me.

33:08.830 --> 33:10.821
Based on what?
Nothing, really.

33:10.830 --> 33:13.321
Hurt feelings. Lies.

33:13.330 --> 33:14.661
Are you gonna
do something about it?

33:14.670 --> 33:16.490
Well, there's nothing
I can do.

33:16.500 --> 33:18.786
I just have to see
how it all plays out.

33:18.790 --> 33:21.111
You're just gonna roll over
and let it happen?

33:21.120 --> 33:22.701
Well --

33:22.710 --> 33:25.076
One of the first things
I learned in basic was,

33:25.080 --> 33:26.786
at a time of war,

33:26.790 --> 33:29.031
you take the fight
to your enemy.

33:29.040 --> 33:31.372
You _can't sit around
clicking your heels,

33:31.380 --> 33:33.871
waiting for unreasonable people
to become reasonable,

33:33.880 --> 33:35.529
because they never will.

33:37.170 --> 33:40.458
You have to take the fight
to your enemy.

33:44.880 --> 33:46.245
[ Sighs ]

33:46.250 --> 33:48.036
Ms. Parios.
What can I do you for?

33:48.040 --> 33:50.998
I'd like to lodge some
complaints against Ginger Lloyd.

33:51.000 --> 33:52.661
Specifically?

33:52.670 --> 33:55.878
Wage violations, employee abuse,
possible aggravated assault,

33:55.880 --> 33:58.997
sexual harassment,
and a hostile work environment.

33:59.000 --> 34:00.911
I'll get a pen.

34:00.920 --> 34:02.535
[ Drawer opens ]

34:17.170 --> 34:18.614
Max: It's a bad call.

34:18.620 --> 34:21.578
If I wanted your opinion,
I would have asked for it.

34:21.580 --> 34:23.207
Fine.

34:23.210 --> 34:25.201
Do whatever
the hell you want.

34:28.500 --> 34:30.036
[Tools clatter ]

34:30.040 --> 34:31.109
[ Sighs ]

34:34.960 --> 34:36.029
You alright?

34:36.040 --> 34:37.780
Nope.

34:37.790 --> 34:40.827
I gotta get
the hell out of here.

34:40.830 --> 34:42.036
You talking away from Leo?

34:42.040 --> 34:43.450
No.
[Tools clatter ]

34:43.460 --> 34:45.416
Just...

34:45.420 --> 34:47.320
out.

34:47.330 --> 34:48.615
Well, maybe I can help.

34:48.620 --> 34:49.996
[ Scoffs ]

34:50.000 --> 34:52.537
You barely know me.

34:52.540 --> 34:53.746
I know enough.

34:56.960 --> 34:59.417
Scuzzy: Grey!

34:59.420 --> 35:01.661
With me. Now.

35:04.580 --> 35:06.878
[ Door opens ]

35:06.880 --> 35:09.531
[Thunder rumbling ]

35:33.790 --> 35:35.701
[ Elevator whirring ]

35:38.580 --> 35:40.741
Hope you got
your story straight.

35:40.750 --> 35:42.456
[ Gate creaks ]

35:45.710 --> 35:47.701
Hey. What's up?

35:47.710 --> 35:49.780
You did time
at Columbia River, right?

35:49.790 --> 35:51.246
Yeah,
I did three years.

35:51.250 --> 35:53.787
And that was what?
2012?

35:53.790 --> 35:55.326
Yeah, sounds right.

35:55.330 --> 35:56.877
You know Billy Galvin?

35:56.880 --> 35:57.949
[ Chuckles ]

36:00.540 --> 36:02.667
I haven't thought
of that name in years.

36:03.880 --> 36:05.780
He told me
a funny story recently.

36:05.790 --> 36:07.109
Oh, yeah?

36:07.120 --> 36:09.327
I don't remember him
being too funny.

36:09.330 --> 36:11.286
Yeah, well, I told him
you were working with us.

36:13.120 --> 36:15.031
And he told me
to be careful.

36:16.540 --> 36:17.871
Hmm.

36:17.880 --> 36:19.165
Just so
I get this straight --

36:19.170 --> 36:21.821
you called that dude
to check up on me?

36:21.830 --> 36:24.537
You know, he'd sell his mother
out for a pack of gum.

36:24.540 --> 36:25.666
'Cause he's a snitch.

36:25.670 --> 36:27.376
Maybe it takes one
to know one.

36:34.960 --> 36:37.417
What's going on here?
Are you bored?

36:37.420 --> 36:38.660
Is that what this is?

36:38.670 --> 36:40.535
'Cause you'd have to be
bored and stupid

36:40.540 --> 36:43.031
to take a guy like Billy Galvin
at his word, Leo.

36:44.750 --> 36:46.536
Alright, let's do this.

36:46.540 --> 36:48.246
Why don't you find me
when you're ready to
move your weight?

36:48.250 --> 36:50.115
Otherwise, find somebody else
to play tough guy with.

36:53.290 --> 36:55.611
[ Glass rattles ]

36:57.080 --> 36:57.819
Hey.

36:59.960 --> 37:01.951
I'll meet your buyer.

37:01.960 --> 37:04.827
Okay, no guarantees,
but we can have a sit-down.

37:04.830 --> 37:06.036
Where they at?

37:09.880 --> 37:12.030
Los Angeles.
Good.

37:12.040 --> 37:13.746
Have them here
tomorrow afternoon.

37:13.750 --> 37:15.320
Okay.

37:15.330 --> 37:17.707
[ Gate creaks, clicks ]

37:17.710 --> 37:20.110
[ Elevator whirring ]

37:24.580 --> 37:25.535
Hoffman: Arrieta.

37:29.620 --> 37:31.827
You're looking for 20 kilos,
you got the wrong warehouse.

37:37.750 --> 37:39.320
Wow.

37:39.330 --> 37:41.571
You're a jackass
and you're dirty.

37:41.580 --> 37:43.616
What are you
talking about?

37:43.620 --> 37:45.918
I got a call from this location.
They said they needed backup.

37:45.920 --> 37:49.242
Stole a dummy file
off my desk.

37:49.250 --> 37:51.616
So...

37:51.620 --> 37:54.612
you're on the take with
whoever got their heroin stolen?

37:58.750 --> 38:00.069
I'm not telling you squat.

38:00.080 --> 38:01.411
Mm.

38:01.420 --> 38:03.115
Then maybe
you'll tell me.

38:07.330 --> 38:08.877
Bobby.

38:08.880 --> 38:11.110
It's not
what it looks like.

38:11.120 --> 38:13.168
Come on.
You know me.

38:14.540 --> 38:15.780
I used to.

38:17.710 --> 38:20.031
He's all yours.

38:20.040 --> 38:21.701
Give me your hands.

38:21.710 --> 38:22.995
Bring them up.

38:24.250 --> 38:26.457
You have the right
to remain silent.

38:26.460 --> 38:28.030
Anything you say can
and will be used against you

38:28.040 --> 38:29.246
in a court of law.

38:29.250 --> 38:31.912
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

38:31.920 --> 38:33.410
[ Cellphone beeps ]

38:33.420 --> 38:34.318
Grey, what's up?

38:36.880 --> 38:37.949
Tomorrow?

38:40.250 --> 38:43.242
Come on, come on, come
Oh, nah, nah

38:43.250 --> 38:45.912
Come on, come on, come on
Ooh, son...

38:45.920 --> 38:47.785
Oh.

38:47.790 --> 38:48.575
Buy you a drink?

38:48.580 --> 38:50.536
No, I'm good.

38:50.540 --> 38:54.453
So, I've decided to give Enrique
a job until his knee heals.

38:54.460 --> 38:56.280
Oh. Wow.
That's big of you.

38:56.290 --> 38:57.996
Well, that club
means everything to me.

38:58.000 --> 38:59.820
I know it seems like
I have it together

38:59.830 --> 39:01.411
and everything's perfect,

39:01.420 --> 39:03.741
but without that place,
I'd be a mess.

39:03.750 --> 39:05.957
I have to protect myself.

39:05.960 --> 39:07.575
I may have overreacted.

39:07.580 --> 39:08.911
You think?

39:08.920 --> 39:10.410
Do you want
your necklace back?

39:10.420 --> 39:13.071
I want you to drop
the complaints against me.

39:13.080 --> 39:15.492
The club is all you have.
Being a PI is all I have.

39:17.210 --> 39:18.700
I'll drop mine
if you drop yours.

39:21.540 --> 39:22.871
Deal.

39:22.880 --> 39:24.780
Hmm.

39:24.790 --> 39:27.827
No one's ever gone
toe-to-toe with me and won.

39:27.830 --> 39:29.161
I knew I liked you.

39:30.540 --> 39:31.746
See ya 'round, toots.

39:31.750 --> 39:33.957
[ Billiard balls clack]

39:33.960 --> 39:36.952
La la la la

39:36.960 --> 39:40.168
La la la la

39:44.710 --> 39:45.665
Lieutenant.

39:47.040 --> 39:48.826
Go ahead.

39:48.830 --> 39:50.377
You told me so.

39:50.380 --> 39:53.611
I would, if it would
make me feel any better.

39:53.620 --> 39:56.077
So...
what's the plan now?

39:56.080 --> 39:57.911
We move forward.

39:57.920 --> 40:00.320
I get someone
to front as a buyer.

40:00.330 --> 40:03.117
Okay.
Reach out to narcotics.

40:03.120 --> 40:04.747
See who they've got
working undercover.

40:04.750 --> 40:06.377
After this?

40:06.380 --> 40:08.245
No way.
[ Exhales sharply]

40:08.250 --> 40:09.786
Well, then,
who are you gonna use?

40:09.790 --> 40:10.666
I'll get an informant.

40:10.670 --> 40:11.534
VVho?

40:15.330 --> 40:17.457
I'll get you
the paperwork later.

40:17.460 --> 40:19.917
Hoffman.

40:19.920 --> 40:21.490
Look.
[ Exhales sharply]
I don't know
about this, man.

40:21.500 --> 40:22.990
Why don't you just get
one of your cops

40:23.000 --> 40:24.490
to stand in as the buyer?

40:24.500 --> 40:27.617
After today, I need somebody
I know I can trust.

40:27.620 --> 40:29.952
[ Extreme's "One More Body"
plays ]

40:32.170 --> 40:34.821
Mister,
can you hear my name?

40:34.830 --> 40:37.321
[ Chuckles ]
Wow!

40:37.330 --> 40:39.207
Buddy, is this
what you've been working on?

40:39.210 --> 40:41.166
It's for you.
It's for me?

40:41.170 --> 40:42.706
W-What is it?

40:42.710 --> 40:44.109
I'll give you a hint.

40:46.080 --> 40:47.490
Fuego.
VVhoa!

40:47.500 --> 40:48.535
[ Laughs ]

40:52.080 --> 40:53.035
Remember now?

40:55.920 --> 40:57.785
Today was the day

40:57.790 --> 41:00.577
you came to get me

41:00.580 --> 41:01.820
12 years ago.

41:03.420 --> 41:04.956
That's right.

41:04.960 --> 41:06.700
And, uh --
And we went to Romy's Diner,

41:06.710 --> 41:08.450
and I got you...

41:08.460 --> 41:10.166
a slice of Baked Alaska.

41:12.250 --> 41:14.411
You told me
everything would be okay.

41:14.420 --> 41:17.321
I did,
and I meant that.

41:17.330 --> 41:19.321
You know I'm always gonna be
here for you, buddy, right?

41:19.330 --> 41:21.616
And I'll always
be here for you.

41:21.620 --> 41:23.997
Come here.

41:24.000 --> 41:25.319
This is awesome.
Thank you so much.

41:25.330 --> 41:26.536
Hoffman: Dex.

41:26.540 --> 41:27.780
Wow. Hey, guys.

41:27.790 --> 41:29.610
Do you, uh, want some cake?

41:29.620 --> 41:30.917
What's going on?

41:30.920 --> 41:31.818
We need your help, Dex.

41:33.210 --> 41:34.416
Like, right now.
